metadata.name: Aftershock #11
metadata.description:
Turkey was hit by two devastating earthquakes at 6/02/2023 effecting multiple cities.

Aftershock is created to help and support people in earthquake region. 100% of the revenue from primary sales will be send to non governmental organization AHBAP after it's converted to ethereum. All donation will sent from atimtay.eth and will be shared publicly from my twitter account


Artwork info:

Aftershock is based on "Metropolix IX' algorithm. In Metropolis the parameter space was constrained and the cells were painted in a fashion which would create city silhouettes. In Aftershock i removed the constraints and changed the all rulesets and palettes which would give us chaos maybe you can call it a collapsed city.


Features:

6 color palettes and 1 monochrome 
3 subdivison levels 2,3,4 
2 aspect ratios 
10 divison styles 
and some other hidden randomized parameters which doesn't appear on the features but effecting overall outcome

Press 1 to 8 to export PNG at increasing resolution

Murat Atimtay 2023 www.atimtay.xyz

metadata.name: Tempus Fugit #38
metadata.description:
This collection combines several classical techniques (Isometric 3D, voxels, noise fields, and unusual Truchet tilings) into something new.

In some pieces, the base 3d structure dissolves, creating an abstract, twisted painting
with only an elusive sense of the underlying construction logic.

Others are more architectural. Are they decaying cities from another age ? Deteriorating landscapes for the Minecraft generation ? Strange artifacts from a long gone alien civilization ? The viewer will decide.

All iterations, though, are designed to express this common feeling that time erodes everything. Tempus Fugit.


Made with p5.js only (no webgl).

Key commands:
's' - save to png
'1', '2, '4' - change resolution

metadata.name: LA BOUGIE ð¯ #24
metadata.description:
This work is a collection along the lines of abstract works that I produced during the last year, and this is the first generative project in the form of a collaboration with the artist's friend Arash. This is the beginning of the production of fascinating works that we have been working on for several projects for months. In the background of this piece, there is a combination of Mondrian's known works with his well-known color palette and style, and the compositions try to remember Mondrian's works and create new and different designs. This deconstruction of The style Art movement continued and flourished with his other contemporary artists; Fx Hash's one-year candle combines de Stijl's work with a new pattern that creates new compositions independent of this work.

Unique collection by ArashMp and Chistai for #fxhashturnsone
